    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can protect yourself by negotiating specific limitations on the indemnity clause. Try to narrow the scope, specifying that you only indemnify them for claims arising from your *direct* infringement or willful misconduct, not for general business risks they take on. Also, consider adding a \"hold harmless\" carve-out that limits your liability to the contract's total fee, capping your potential financial exposure.",
